/span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> response </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">at</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> Q219</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> of the transcript</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">)</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">SOUTH EAST REGIONAL ORGANISED CRIME UNIT (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">SEROCU</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">- SINGLE COMMAND MODEL FOR COUNTER TERRORISM AND</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">SERIOUS ORGANISED CRIME</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">BACKGROUND</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">To develop the South East region’s capacity and capability to tackle </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">erious and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rganised </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rime, regional Chief Constables and Police and Crime Commissioners have agreed to a new single command model which incorporates regional Counter Terrorism (CT) and Serious and Organised Crime (SOC) assets. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In 2010 Chief Constables and representatives of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">olice </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">uthorities signed Section 23 agreements for the South East Regional Organised Crime Unit (SEROCU), South East Covert Operations (SECOU), South East Technical Surveillance (SETSU) and the South East Protected Person Scheme (SEPPS). These regional units were formed from existing Force capability and based upon a ‘Lead Force’ model with Sussex leading SEROCU, Thames Valley SETSU, Hampshire SEPPS and Surrey SECOU.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> November 2012 three options were </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">considered by the Chief Constables across the South East region </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for the future approach to tackling SOC and CT in the region. The option to develop a single command model incorporating regional CT and SOC assets supported by a common infrastructure was </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">subsequently </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">agreed by the Chief Constables and PCCs. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This initiative is intended to complement the work of the National Crime Agency.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Following this decision a programme of work started with a two phased approach. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The first phase of work is now complete which saw the alignment of the SEROCU, SECOU, SETSU and SEPPS under a single command structure.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Phase Two</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> is now underway with detailed planning taking place to develop and implement the future command model and alignment to the South East Counter Terrorism Unit. Subject to consultation, the HR model for the realigned regional SOC units will be a Thames Valley Police host force model, with a Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) between regional Chief Constables. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In addition to this the Home Office ha</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> given regional organised crime units a grant to fund the development of additional capabilities in serious organised crime. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Accordingly, the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> regional Chief Constables and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Police and Crime Commissioners considered proposals </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to address current capability gaps in confidential unit, prison intelligence, cyber crime and fraud</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and approved the relevant business cases</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Recruitment for the heads of these new regional units has begun and they will be responsible for building and recruiting their team. They will be employed by the host force (Thames Valley Police) and will sit within the current regional organised crime unit structure.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">An </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Assistant Chief Constable has been appointed to lead the new regional CT and SOC command, working for and accountable to the whole region and all five Chief Constables, tak</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">g</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> up the role with effect from 1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">st</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> October 2013.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The timescales for the completion for this </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">second </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">phase is April 2014, which includes the first implementation phase for the additional capabilities.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">SE ROCU </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">BUSINESS CASE</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The vision for the South East </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Regional</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Organised Crime and Counter Terrorism Command for the forces of Surrey, Sussex, Kent, Hampshire and Thames Valley Police is:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="OLE_LINK4"></a><a name="OLE_LINK3"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">“To create a cohesive regional response to serious organised crime aligned to the current South East Counter Terrorism unit.  Delivering enhanced interoperability and resilience across the region supporting all local Forces as well as national agencies and capabilities.”</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The work to build a South East Regional</span><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Organised Crime Unit (SEROCU) is driven by a number of key factors including:- </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The ‘Local to Global’ report. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Home Secretary’s strategic aim to tackle serious and organised crime. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The development of the National Crime Agency and plan to further develop the national policing landscape. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The enhanced understanding of the levels of threat and risk as evidenced by the Organised Crime Group Mapping work. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Strategic Policing Requirement and the ACPO National Capabilities work. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The HMIC ‘Street to Strategic’ inspection of Forces and agencies responses to serious and organised crime. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">hief </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">onstable</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Mick </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Creedon’s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> report dated September 2011 on the required capabilities required by Forces to ensure they could effectively tackle serious and organised crime. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">hief </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">onstable</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Mick </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Creedon’s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> review of Regional Organised Crime Units dated April 2012 provided to the National Police Protective Services Steering Group. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">national </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">review of Regional Organised Crime Units identified that there is not a consistent national network to link to national agencies, and presented a professional approach that seeks to define what functions, capacity and capability should be hosted within the regional structure.  It stated that it is never intended that the regional function provides for the entire requirement for the region and the host Forces; rather that the regional function provides the more specialist niche capability in a consistent manner that is both operationally and financially efficient.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">These </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">regional </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">functions are:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Intelligence – the regional intelligence unit</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Confidential intelligence – a confidential unit</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">3. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Covert policing – a collaborative approach to delivering and managing undercover operations and activity</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Financial investigation and asset recovery team – the regional asset recovery teams</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">5. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Fraud investigation – the potential for the regional fraud investigation teams</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">6. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Technical surveillance</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">7. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Protected persons/witness protection</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">8. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Cyber crime and e-crime</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">9. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Operational Security</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">10. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">GAIN – the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Government Agency Intelligence Network</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">’</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">11. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Prison Intelligence</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">12. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Operational Investigative Teams</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">national </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">review of the ROCUs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">made reference to the possible </span><a name="OLE_LINK2"></a><a name="OLE_LINK1"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">synergies and efficiencies with the counter terrorism (CT) infrastructure, in particular around issues such as sharing accommodation, sharing leadership, sharing back office support and at times sharing specialist assets. </span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> It was recognised that the policing response to serious and organised crime is not the same as that required to tackle terrorism, and this position is based upon the day to day impact and the hugely diverse nature of the criminality – requiring an overall approach from neighbourhood policing upwards.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Whilst the South East region has established a strong response to serious organised crime</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">previous (pre-SE ROCU)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> arrangements </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">we</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">re inefficient due to their complexity and there are additional capabilities that can be included within the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">new </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">regional remit. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Having taken account of all these factors, the South East Serious Organised Crime and the South East Counter Terrorism Unit are being aligned, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">facilitated by</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the addition of a Regional A</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ssistant </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">hief </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">onstable </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Serious Organised Crime and Counter Terrorism</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  As the South East Counter Terrorism Unit is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">currently </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">hosted by Thames Valley Police</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the South East </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Regional </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Organised Crime Unit follow</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> this host force model.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_Toc353355528"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></a></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><h1 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">SE ROCU Model</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> - </span><a name="_Toc353355527"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Remit</span></a></h1><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The South East Regional Organised Crime Unit will bring together the current regional organised crime units under the one structure:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Regional Investigation Unit</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Regional Asset Recovery Unit</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Regional Intelligence Unit</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Regional Covert Operations Unit</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Regional Witness Protection Unit</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Regional Technical Surveillance Unit</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Additional capabilities be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(or being assessed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> included</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> within the regional structure</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> are</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Fraud</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Cyber Crime &amp; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">eCrime</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Operational Security</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Government Agency Intelligence Network</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Prison Intelligence</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Operational Investigation Team</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Confidential Unit</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The services, governed under the umbrella of a Police and Crime Commissioners’ Section 22A Police Act agreement, will incorporate:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A unified regional management structure with clear lines of reporting and accountability.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Standardised processes and procedures.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">IT platforms enabling regional user inter</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">operability.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Regionally agreed working practices.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Efficiencies/ Benefits</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">When t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he new arrangements </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">are fully in place with effect from April 2014 they </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will create a unified Serious Organised Crime Unit for the S</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">outh </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">E</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ast </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">region </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">that will deliver the following benefits</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Builds upon established performance thereby maximising our potential.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Aligns the South East Serious Organised Crime and South East Counter Terrorism Unit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> into a single command model.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Increased operability</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Joint management of assets and flexibility in tasking</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Provides resilience to the units across the region.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Complements national agencies</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Aligned </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and more efficient </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">operational and business support</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Maximises economies of scale, efficiency gains and savings</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Is recognised as a model of good practice.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Provides career development opportunities for our staff.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Aligned performance reporting </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> -  a single data set and return for the South East</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A single command model will provide a better, less complex, basis for any rationalisation/restructuring which may be required in the future</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The unified unit i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s accountable to the Chief Constables and PCCs across the region</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The overall benefit of a single command structure will be the regional overview of the provision and capability of serious organised crime units and the value for money provided locally, regionally and nationally</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Financ</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">ial Implications</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Set Up Costs</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The cost of implementing this programme of work will be mainly staff opportunity costs.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Home Office is providing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">funding</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to support Regional Organised Crime Unit networks</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, including </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">additional investment for the financial year 2013/14.  Th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">additional </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">investment </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">fund</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> is available to strengthen the region’s resilience against organised crime.  Th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Home Office investment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> will need to be matched locally by the same level of investment and commitment.  In many cases this </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">can</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> be met by redeploying existing operational resources rather than a call on new monetary resources.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><a name="_Toc353355539"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Finance Model</span></a></h2><h2 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">&#xa0;</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The draft 2014/15 spending budget for the SE ROCU is £11.5m.  The source of funding for the Unit </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to cover this level of planned spending </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">£8.2m contributions from the five forces and £3.3m from Government grants.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Previously,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> a lead force approach has been adopted for the current regional serious organised crime units </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">under which </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">it was the lead force’s responsibility to provide business support to the unit.  A principle was agreed that the lead force for each of the units could charge 2% of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">unit </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">salary costs to the other forces </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to help cover the cost to the lead force of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the provision of business support.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There is likely to be a cost implication of transferring con</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">trol of the agreed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">SEROCU </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">units to T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">hames </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">V</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">alley </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">P</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">olice</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This will arise from increasing the business support functions in SE Counter Terrorism Unit (SECTU) to cope with the SOC assets. There will however be compensating savings for each force </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">by the removal of the 2% charge </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">currently </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">levied by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the four separate SE </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">lead </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">forces on </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">individual unit </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">salary costs. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In setting up the South East Regional Organised Crime Units under a host force model it is assumed that the overall </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration:underline">budget</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> for the unit will remain the same (increasing in line with inflation).  However, the new, single, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">host f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">orce is responsible for all business support and administration, including HR, Finance, Procurement and Estates.  This will provide economies of scale compared to the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">current provision by four lead forces that will release cost savings and/or service productivity gains. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The build of this </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">single </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">command </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">model </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will also provide an opportunity to revisit the current funding model for regional units and the provision of business support.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Accordingly, work is currently underway to produce the regional ‘Collaboration Finance Protocol and Principles’ </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(to be incorporated into the S22A Agreement) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and a ‘Principles for a Cost Apportionment Model’ for approval and adoption for both this SE ROCU collaboration model and all other future SE Region collaborations.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Collaboration </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Risks </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The following risks have been identified in relation to the regional delivery of serious organised crime and counter terrorism:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Loss of skills - there is a risk that key skills will be lost as staff </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">may </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">seek employment elsewhere.  This will impact on the ability of units to maintain business as usual.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Staff morale - there is a risk that morale will decline due to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">change fatigue</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> which </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">may</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> impact on performance.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">3. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Inadequate project resourcing - there is a risk that inadequate project resourcing will undermine project delivery and cause delays.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Internal Change Programmes - conflict of priorities with individual internal </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">force </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">change programmes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> e.g. estates strategies.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">5. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Perceived risk to transparency of tasking - CT assets are nationally owned and co-ordinated and regionally based</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> whereas SOC assets are locally owned and regionally based.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">6. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Perceived risk to command/ownership - a host f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">orce model is being </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">adopt</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ed;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the perception could be that the host force would provide the sole command rather than the reality of it being a regional command of regional assets.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Risk mitigation action plans have been developed and implemented to address and minimise these risks.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">GOVERNANCE</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The PCCs and Chief Constables across the South East region established a ‘Regional Collaboration Gov</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ernance Board’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in July 2013</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The membership of the Board comprises the PCCs and chief constables of all the force areas across the South East. The Board is scheduled to meet quarterly and minutes of all meetings will be taken.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Board will:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Assist the PCCs and chief constables to have a mutually supportive relationship</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, consistent with the principles set out in the Policing Protocol</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Set the strategic direction for regional working.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Approve an annual </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Board </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">business plan.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Consider and approve the business plans of proposed collaborative service initiatives and associated S22A agreements.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Provide</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> oversight and scrutiny of the activities and performance of the SE ROCU and CTU, and any other services to be provided on a regional basis in the future</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Ensure PCCs and chief constables are sighted upon the national agenda</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> as it develops (e.g. the relationship with the National Crime Agency; HMIC inspection of the Strategic Policing Requirement)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">F</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">acilitate the PCCs to discharge their statutory duty, individually and collectively, to hold chief constables to account for delivery of services provided in collaboration on a regional basis.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I hope you find the information presented above</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> concerning collaboration activity across the South East region both</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> informative and useful to your Committee’s enquiries.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">If you require any further information, please do not hesitate to contact my office.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Anthony Stansfeld</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Police and Crime Commissioner for Thames Valley</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">27</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> January 2014</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Background </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Source </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Documents:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Papers presented to the Extraordinary Meeting of the South-East Police and Crime Commissioners and Chief Constables held on 5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> July 2013:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-42.5pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Item 5 - ‘Proposal for a Regional Governance Board’ </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-42.5pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Item 6 – ‘Business Case for South East Regional Organised Crime and Counter Terrorism Command’ (Restricted)  </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Papers presented to the Regional Collaboration Board meeting held on 14</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> January 2014:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-42.5pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Item 6 – ‘SEROCU Programme Performance and Finance Update’:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 63.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Appendix 3 - Principles for a Cost Apportionment Formula</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 63.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Appendix 4 – Collaboration Finance Protocols and Principles</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>